#Text=The Phoenix Suns ( 34 - 32 ) defeated the Minnesota Timberwolves ( 14 - 49 ) 106 - 97 on Wednesday at the US Airways Center in Phoenix .
#Text=The Suns got out to a quick start in this one , grabbing a 25 - 18 lead right away after the first quarter .

#Text=It remained pretty much even throughout the rest of the game , but the Suns were able to pull off a huge win , as it put them just two and a half games out of the final projected playoff seed in the Western Conference standings .

#Text=The Suns were the superior shooters in this game , going 50 percent from the field and 25 percent from the three - point line , while the Timberwolves finished at just 44 percent from the floor and a disgraceful eight percent from beyond the arc .
#Text=The Suns were led by Markieff Morris , who finished with a team - high of 24 points ( 10 - 15 FG , 0 - 2 3Pt , 4 - 4 FT ) , to go along with three rebounds and two assists in 37 minutes .
#Text=It was a very nice bounce - back outing for the forward , as he posted just four points on 1 - of - 8 shooting from the field during Monday 's game against the Warriors .
#Text=He 's now averaging 15 points and 6 rebounds on the year .
#Text=Also getting a piece of the action was Eric Bledsoe , who had a great night shooting the ball to finish with 18 points ( 7 - 14 FG , 2 - 5 3Pt , 2 - 2 FT ) and nine assists .
#Text=It was his second strong showing in a row , as he 's combined for 37 points and 12 assists over his last two games .
#Text=The Suns gained even more of an advantage from their bench in the win , as they were extremely productive .
#Text=Rookie T.J.
#Text=Warren had a breakout performance and scored 17 points ( 8 - 10 FG , 0 - 1 3Pt , 1 - 2 FT ) in just 19 minutes .
#Text=The Suns drafted him knowing he could score at a high rate , so it 's not surprising he was finally able to show a little more of what he 's got .
#Text=Marcus Thornton also reached double figures off the bench , with 14 points ( 6 - 12 FG , 1 - 5 3Pt , 1 - 1 FT ) and four rebounds in 22 minutes .
#Text=Kevin Martin did his best to keep the Timberwolves in this game .
#Text=He went 5 - for - 8 from the field and 6 - for - 7 from the free throw line to score a team - high of 16 points .
#Text=After shooting just 25 percent ( 2 - 8 FG ) from the field in Monday 's game against the Clippers , it was good to see him hit on such a high percentage of shots Wednesday .

#Text=In a solid performance off the bench , Justin Hamilton went 7 - for - 12 from the field and 1 - for - 4 from the three - point line to score a season - high of 15 points , while also adding three rebounds and two blocked shots .
#Text=It was a nice surprise for the Timberwolves , as he averages just 3 points per game and has reached double - digit points in just one other game this season .
#Text=With Kevin Garnett sitting out on a night of rest , Adreian Payne moved back into the starting lineup for the fourth time this season .
#Text=In 29 minutes , he finished with 10 points ( 3 - 9 FG , 4 - 4 FT ) and three rebounds .
#Text=Andrew Wiggins did n't have much of an impact either , as he also had just 10 points ( 5 - 11 FG , 0 - 1 3Pt ) and four rebounds .
#Text=The Suns ' next game will be at home against the Atlanta Hawks on Friday , while the Timberwolves will travel to Oklahoma City to play the Thunder on Friday .
